OL,3,CConservation group warns rivers are
OL,4,Cbeing contaminated due to blocked
OL,5,Cdrains
OL,7,FResponding to the criticisms about
OL,8,Fagricultural runoff, a spokesperson
OL,9,Ffor the National Farmers' Union said:
OL,10,F"Farmers and growers care about water
OL,11,Fquality in rivers and we continue to
OL,12,Fwork hard, through a range of
OL,13,Fmeasures, to prevent valuable
OL,14,Fnutrients and soil that are crucial to
OL,15,Four farming systems and producing
OL,16,Ffood, from contributing to water
OL,17,Fpollution."
